                        <summary/>
                        
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="1ra" to="97rb"/>
                            <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7510HagDosAA">Hagiographic dossier of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            
                       <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                            <locus from="1ra" to="72ra"/>
                           <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1409GadlaA">Gadla ʾAbrǝhā wa-ʾAṣbǝḥa</title>
                           <note>The birthday of the two saints is celebrated on <date ref="ethiocal:Tahsas29">29 Tāḫśāś</date> and the entry of their
                               bodies into the sanctuary (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝውእቱ፡ በዓለ፡ ደብረ፡ ታቦር፡ በዘቦአ፡ ሥጋሆሙ፡ ውስተ፡
                                   ቤተ፡ መቅደስ።</foreign>) on <date ref="ethiocal:Nahase13">13 Naḥase</date>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                                በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አብ፡ ዘኢይትፌከር፡ ወዘኢይትነገር። አልቦ፡ ንጉሥ፡
                                ዘእንበሌሁ፡ በሰማይ፡ ወምድር። ወበስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወልድ፡ ዘዕሩይ፡ ምክሩ፡ ምስለ፡ አቡሁ። ወምስለ፡
                                መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ እምአብ፡ ዘይወጽእ፡ ወእምወልድ፡ ዘይነሥእ፡ ገድል፡ ወሰምዕ፡ ዘአብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ ነገሥተ፡ አክሱም፡ 
                                ዘነበበ፡ በመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አባ፡ ሰላማ፡ ጳጳስ፡ ዘኢትዮጵያ። ወተጽሕፈ፡ በእደዊሆሙ፡ ለሌዋውያን፡ ካሀናት፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ 
                                ወገብረ፡ መስቀል። ዘወለጡ፡ መጻሕ<supplied reason="omitted">ፍ</supplied>ተ፡
                                እምዓረቢ፡ ለግዕዝ፡ <sic>ለብሔረ፡</sic> ኢትዮጵያ፡ በመዋዕሊ<cb n="b"/>ሆሙ፡ ለአብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ
                                ነገሥተ፡ አክሱም፡ ጸሎቶሙ፡ ወበረከቶሙ፡ ለእሉ፡ ነገሥት፡ ክቡራን፡<surplus>፡</surplus> የሃሉ፡ መስለ፡ 
                                ፍቁሮሙ፡</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                            
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                                <locus from="72ra" to="87vb"/>
                                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7511TaammeraAA">Taʾammǝra ʾAbrǝhā wa-ʾAṣbǝḥa</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">    
                                    በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/>                 
                                    ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ ብርሃናተ፡ ዓለም፡
                                  </incipit>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.1">
                                    <locus from="72ra" to="72vb"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7517MAAResuscitation">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa are transported after their death by the order of the Lord to the town of Gamād, where they resuscitate a rich and glorious man who died during the journey</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">                    
                                        በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ ብርሃናተ፡ 
                                        ዓለም <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ወሶበ፡ አዕረፉ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ አዘዘ፡ እግዚእነ፡ 
                                        ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ከመ፡ ይፁሩ፡ ሥጋ<cb n="b"/>ሆሙ፡ መሐይምናን። 
                                        ወአብጽሕዎሙ፡ ኀበ፡ ሀገረ፡ ገማድ፡
                                </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.2">
                                    <locus from="72vb" to="73vb"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7518MAAChurch">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa help King ʾAnbassā Wǝdǝm, son of King ʾAsfaḥ, to build a church in Wambartā dedicated to St Michael</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">                       
                                        ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ 
                                        <gap reason="ellipsis"/><pb n="73r"/><cb n="a"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/> ወእምድኅረ፡ ሞተ፡ አስፋሕ፡ ንጉሥ። ነግሠ፡ ወልዱ፡
                                        አንበሳ፡ <surplus>አንበሳ፡</surplus> ውድም፡ ወኮነ፡ ፈራሄ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወየአምር፡ ጥበበ፡ ወፍትሐ። ወሐለየ፡ 
                                        በልቡ፡ ከመ፡ ይሕንጽ፡ መቅደሰ፡ ዘአብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ ነገሥተ፡ አክሱም።
                                     </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.3">
                                    <locus from="74ra" to="76ra"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7519MAAHealing">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa heal a blind person</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">                  
                                        ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ወሀሎ፡ ብእሲ፡
                                        ዘዖራ፡ አዕይንቲሁ፡ <choice><corr>በሕማመ፡</corr><sic>በሕማበ፡</sic></choice> በደዶ።
                                     </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.4">
                                    <locus from="76ra" to="77rb"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7520MAADebt">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa give wealth to a poor man who had borrowed two denarii; he then refuses to return them; finally, he repents, pays back his debt and offers half of his goods to the church</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">               
                                        ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/><cb n="b"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/>
                                        ወሀሎ፡ ፩ ብእሲ፡ ዘአኀዞ፡ ንዴት፡ ወምንዳቤ፤ ይቤሎ፡ ለ፩ ባዕል፡ ኦእግዚእየ፡ ሀበኒ፡ ወርቀ፡ ከመ፡ እንግድ፡ 
                                   </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.5">
                                    <locus from="77rb" to="78rb"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7521MAADemon">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: The noonday demon which tormented a woman is chased away by a priest during the feast of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">        
                                        ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/><pb n="77v"/><cb n="a"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/>
                                        ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ዘአኀዛ፡ ጋኔነ፡ ቀትር፡ ወያወድቃ፡ ኵሎ፡ ጊዜ፡
                                        ማእከለ፡ ጕባዔ። ወያሴውና፡ ወያስተራግጻ።
                                    </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.6">
                                    <locus from="78rb" to="79vb"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7522MAAChild">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: Story of a man who had a child thanks to the relics of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa; fulfilling a vow, he brings gifts with his family to the church and is attacked by robbers</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ 
                                        <gap reason="ellipsis"/><pb n="78v"/><cb n="a"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/> 
                                        ወሀሎ፡ ፩ ብእሲ፡ እምርኁቅ፡ ብሔር፡ ወአል<supplied reason="omitted">ቦ</supplied>ቱ፡ 
                                        ውሉድ። ወየሐዝን፡ ፈድፋደ፡ በእንተ፡ ኃጢአ፡ ውሉድ። ወበዊዖ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ መቅደስ፡ ጊዜ፡
                                        መንፈቀ፡ ሌሊት፡ በዕለተ፡ በዓሎሙ፡ ለአብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡
                                    </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.7">
                                    <locus from="79vb" to="80vb"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7523MAAPriests">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa decide the argument between the priests of Gamād and the inhabitants of Garʿaltā in favor of the priests of Gamād</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">                  
                                        ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/><pb n="80r"/><cb n="a"/> ወኮነ፡ በ፩ እመዋዕል፡ ጋዕዝ፡ ወተስናን፡ ማእከሌሆሙ፡ ለካህናተ፡ ገማድ፡ 
                                        ወሰብአ፡ ገርዓልታ፡ ወይቤሉ፡ ሰብአ፡ ገርዓልታ፡ ኢትምጽኡ፡ ኅበ፡ ምድረ፡ መንዳዕ፡ ወኢትልክፍዋ። ዘዚአነ፡ 
                                        ይእቲ፡ ርስተ፡ አበዊነ፡
                               </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.8">
                                    <locus from="80vb" to="81vb"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7524MAAKaleb">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa appear to King Kāleb and help him to vanquish the Jews after the massacre of the Christians of Nāgrān</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">               
                                        ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/><pb n="81r"/><cb n="a"/> ወአመ፡ ነግሠ፡ ካሌብ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ተንሥኡ፡ ዓረብ፡ ትሩፋነ፡ አይሁድ። 
                                        እምሀገረ፡ ሳባ። ወበጽሑ፡ ሀገረ፡ ናግራን፡ ወቀተልዎሙ፡ ለሰብእ፡ ወኢያትረፉ፡ ምንተኒ፡
                                        ወበርበሩ፡ ኵሎ፡ ንዋያቲሃ።
                                   </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.9">
                                    <locus from="81vb" to="83va"/>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: King Zarʿa Yāʿqob decides an argument between the priests of Gamād and the priests of ʾAksum on the tithe in favour of the priests of ʾAksum, but after the intervention of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa he changes his decisions and lets the priests of Gamād benefit from their ancient privileges</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">              
                                        ተአምር፡ ዘገብሩ፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/><pb n="82r"/><cb n="a"/> ወበመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ዘርዓ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ ዘተሰምየ፡
                                        ቈስጠንጢኖስ፡ ተበዓሉ፡ ካህናተ፡ ገማድ፡ ወካህናተ፡ አክሱም። ወይቤልዎሙ፡ ሀቡነ፡ አስራተ፡ ዘወሀቡነ፡ አበዊነ፡
                                        ነገሥት፡ አብርሃ፡ ወአጽብሐ። ወይቤሉ፡ እሙንቱ፡ ካህናተ፡ አክሱም። ንሕነሰ፡ ኢነአምር፡ አልብነ፡ ክፍል፡ 
                                        ምስሌክ<cb n="b"/>ሙ።
                                    </incipit>
                                </msItem>
                                
                                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.10">
                                    <locus from="83va" to="85ra"/>
                                    <note>The catalogue indicates that the miracle ends on 
                                    <locus target="#75ra"/>, but this must be an error.</note>
                                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7526MAAGrann">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: During the war of Grāññ, King Lǝbna Dǝngǝl flees and abandons Tǝgrāy; Grāññ promises to his wife Gʷǝdit the riches of the church of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa in Gamād; finally, she repents and hands back the stolen good; she dies and is interred in Ṣǝrāʿ</title>
                                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">             
